  plantName: Tree Stump
  description: A tree stump is the base portion of a tree, including the roots, that
    remains in the ground after the trunk has been cut or broken. It signifies a
    remaining, rooted part of a tree, often used to study tree age (dendrochronology)
    or as a foundation for new growth (coppicing).
